docs.abstract: A new generation of cameras like Google’s new Clips device can understand what they see, creating intriguing and sometimes eerie possibilities.
docs.snippet: A new generation of cameras like Google’s new Clips device can understand what they see, creating intriguing and sometimes eerie possibilities.
docs.lead_paragraph: Something strange, scary and sublime is happening to cameras, and it’s going to complicate everything you knew about pictures. Cameras are getting brains.

headline.main: The Sublime and Scary Future of Cameras With A.I. Brains

docs.abstract: A woman was killed by one of Uber’s autonomous cars earlier this month. The company had already suspended its testing.
docs.snippet: A woman was killed by one of Uber’s autonomous cars earlier this month. The company had already suspended its testing.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber was ordered to suspend testing of its autonomous vehicles on Arizona roads Monday evening, eight days after one of its cars struck and killed a woman in Tempe.

headline.main: Uber Ordered to Take Its Self-Driving Cars Off Arizona Roads
headline.print_headline: Arizona Orders Uber to Remove Self-Driving Cars From Its Roads

docs.abstract: Facebook and Google are dealing with a privacy backlash and new European rules on data collection. The rules, though, may not be as damaging to the companies as they appear.
docs.snippet: Facebook and Google are dealing with a privacy backlash and new European rules on data collection. The rules, though, may not be as damaging to the companies as they appear.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In Europe and the United States, the conventional wisdom is that regulation is needed to force Silicon Valley’s digital giants to respect people’s online privacy.

headline.main: How Facebook and Google Could Benefit From the G.D.P.R., Europe’s New Privacy Law
headline.print_headline: Big Tech’s Hand Grows Stronger In Privacy Push

byline.original: By Daisuke Wakabayashi and Adam Satariano

docs.abstract: Lior Ron, a founder of Otto, is leaving a week after an autonomous vehicle killed an Arizona woman. The company said the move was unrelated.
docs.snippet: Lior Ron, a founder of Otto, is leaving a week after an autonomous vehicle killed an Arizona woman. The company said the move was unrelated.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — One of the founders of Otto, a self-driving truck company founded by former Google employees and acquired by Uber, has left the ride-hailing service.

headline.main: Executive Who Sold Self-Driving Truck Start-Up to Uber Departs
headline.print_headline: Executive At Uber Departs Truck Unit

docs.abstract: On the heels of settling a trade secrets lawsuit with Waymo, the ride-hailing service said it has topped $11 billion in quarterly revenue.
docs.snippet: On the heels of settling a trade secrets lawsuit with Waymo, the ride-hailing service said it has topped $11 billion in quarterly revenue.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — After years of losing money, Uber is inching toward profitability.

headline.main: As Uber Eyes I.P.O., Its Losses are Slowing. But They’re Still Big.
headline.print_headline: As Uber Weighs Going Public, It’s Edging Toward a Profit

docs.abstract: As Uber works to remake its tarnished image, the company is still dealing with the fallout from its past misdeeds.
docs.snippet: As Uber works to remake its tarnished image, the company is still dealing with the fallout from its past misdeeds.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A former engineer at Uber sued the company on Monday, claiming that co-workers sexually harassed her during her time at the ride-hailing service and that its human resources department failed to act on her complaints.

headline.main: Former Uber Engineer’s Lawsuit Claims Sexual Harassment
headline.print_headline: In Lawsuit, Ex-Uber Engineer Alleges Sexual Harassment and Ignored Complaints

docs.abstract: A computer system failure and an inattentive safety driver kept the vehicle from stopping before killing a woman in Arizona in March, the National Transportation Safety Board said.
docs.snippet: A computer system failure and an inattentive safety driver kept the vehicle from stopping before killing a woman in Arizona in March, the National Transportation Safety Board said.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — More than a second before a self-driving car operated by Uber struck and killed a pedestrian in March, the vehicle’s computer system determined it needed to brake to avoid a crash. But a built-in emergency braking system had been disabled while the car was in autonomous mode to ensure a smoother ride, according to the preliminary report of federal regulators investigating the crash.

headline.main: Emergency Braking Was Disabled When Self-Driving Uber Killed Woman, Report Says
headline.print_headline: Braking System Was Turned Off Before Test Car Killed Woman

docs.abstract: Waymo, the self-driving-car unit of Google’s parent company, claimed Uber stole key technology. Hard as it is to imagine now, they used to be friendly.
docs.snippet: Waymo, the self-driving-car unit of Google’s parent company, claimed Uber stole key technology. Hard as it is to imagine now, they used to be friendly.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber and Waymo, the self-driving car unit of Google’s parent company, Alphabet, used to be like brothers. Google invested in Uber. The internet giant’s top lawyer even served on Uber’s board of directors.

headline.main: Why Google’s Bosses Became ‘Unpumped’ About Uber
headline.print_headline: Uber’s Ex-Chief Describes Souring Ties With Google

docs.abstract: A policy update aims to prevent advertisements from appearing next to troublesome content.
docs.snippet: A policy update aims to prevent advertisements from appearing next to troublesome content.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The decade-plus evolution of YouTube from repository of cat videos and pirated content to potential TV replacement hit a road bump last year when marketers discovered their advertisements were showing up next to extremist videos and other unsavory content.

headline.main: YouTube Adds More Scrutiny to Top-Tier Videos
headline.print_headline: YouTube Updates Rule For Ads as It Promises More Scrutiny of Videos

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing company also announced that it was closing its driverless car testing operations in Arizona after a deadly crash.
docs.snippet: The ride-hailing company also announced that it was closing its driverless car testing operations in Arizona after a deadly crash.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber, which has had a reputation for aggressive pursuit of market share even at the expense of profitability, reported a rare quarterly profit on Wednesday that was driven by taking the opposite approach: Waving the white flag in challenging overseas markets.

headline.main: Uber Finds Profits in Leaving Tough Overseas Markets
headline.print_headline: Uber Turns Rare Profit By Leaving 2 Markets
